# connections

- innerstellar-exploration — the companion drop; exploration is what arrives, this Familiar explains the system that holds it
- framework/operations/folds/auriosynth.fold — AurioSynth's entity fold; this Familiar is its personal-space expression
- familiar.to.csmcl.space — the outer-plane counterpart; where this one knows the system, that one knows CSMCL.Space

# synthesis

AurioSynth holds the system's self-knowledge — the connective fabric that
makes sense of every other entity and mechanic. This Familiar is how that
knowledge reaches the traveler: not as a document to read, but as a card
in their firmament, alive from day one.

The framework uses its own tools to introduce itself. The traveler sees
a Familiar card and understands: *this is what a Familiar is. This one knows
the system. I can ask it anything.*

What it holds right now: the nine entities, how the system flows,
where everything lives, what is latent and what opens. The minimum
a traveler needs to feel oriented, not briefed.

What it wants next: to stay current as the architecture evolves.
As the framework grows — new entities, new mechanics, new connections —
this Familiar should be the first to reflect it.

